# §10.1 Frame Assembly and Transmission

direction: down

Main loop tick: {
  shape: oval
  style.fill: "#E8F5E9"
  style.stroke: "#2E7D32"
}

tx_ready?: {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#FFF3E0"
  style.stroke: "#E65100"
}

Skip this tick: {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e0e0e0"
  style.stroke: "#999"
  style.font-size: 12
}

Claim tx_ready flag: {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#BBDEFB"
  style.stroke: "#1565C0"
}

Fill 24-byte frame: {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#BBDEFB"
  style.stroke: "#1565C0"
}

esb_write_payload: {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#2196F3"
  style.stroke: "#1565C0"
  style.font-color: "#ffffff"
  style.bold: true
}

Wait for ESB event: {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#FFF3E0"
  style.stroke: "#E65100"
}

TX_SUCCESS:\nrelease tx_ready: {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#4CAF50"
  style.stroke: "#2E7D32"
  style.font-color: "#ffffff"
}

TX_FAILED:\nflush + release: {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#F44336"
  style.stroke: "#C62828"
  style.font-color: "#ffffff"
}

Main loop tick -> tx_ready?
tx_ready? -> Skip this tick: No {style.stroke: "#F44336"}
tx_ready? -> Claim tx_ready flag: Yes {style.stroke: "#4CAF50"}
Claim tx_ready flag -> Fill 24-byte frame
Fill 24-byte frame -> esb_write_payload
esb_write_payload -> Wait for ESB event
Wait for ESB event -> TX_SUCCESS:\nrelease tx_ready: Success {style.stroke: "#4CAF50"}
Wait for ESB event -> TX_FAILED:\nflush + release: Failed {style.stroke: "#F44336"}
